      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Winning the Nutrition Game, With Help From a Coach'' (April 22), which discussed the hiring of personal coaches to help with weight loss or other goals:</p>
        <p>For many people, the problem is not that they don't know how to eat healthfully but that they don't like to, because of a fact that is apparent to anyone with taste buds: healthful foods simply don't taste as good as ice cream sundaes and chocolate layer cake.</p>
        <p>Felicia Nimue Ackerman  Providence, R.I., April 22</p>
        <p>The writer is a philosophy professor at Brown University.</p>
      </block>
